    "title": "Useful links",
    "body": " Useful links: Take some inspiration from NCRA webste hereA lot of data and softwares are available publicly for free. Be it the database from the Sloan Digital Sky Surey, to the upcoming facilites, a lot of data and the tools to acces them are publicly available nowadays. We just attach links to a few of them, so that interested people may keep a track of them. Of course, members of the CosmicVarta team use a lot of these sofawres and databases on a uusal basis, toards their Ph. D degrees! If you have any problem, you may ask us through the forms available in the contact section, or even in the comments section below. 1. SDSS: 2. GAIA: NED-databases: SIMBAD: SIMBAD is used to search for any object in the sky. Please go through this article about how to use SIMBAD. How to search for any location using SIMBAD? The NASA ADS: arXiv preprint server: The NASA IPAC database: The HEASARC archive. : Other useful Links: NASA public data ESO public archives Astrosat public data Please enable JavaScript to view the comments powered by Disqus. "
